Rain or shine: Tatak 2023 marks newly hatched Falcons

Despite the heat followed by the rain, the Adamson Universityâ€™s new students received their handprint marks in â€œTatak Adamson 2023: Kakulayaan,â€ symbolizing their welcoming rites as Klasmeyts, at Saint Vincent (SV) Grounds, this afternoon. 

The Adamson University Student Government (AUSG) Vice President for Internal Affairs Kyle V. Ronquillo explained the concept of the eventâ€™s title. 

â€œâ€™Yung mark means tatak ni Saint Vincent [â€¦]. â€˜Yung mismong title ngayon is â€˜Tatak Adamson 2023: Kakulayaan.â€™ [â€¦] â€˜Yung Kulay na â€˜yon serves as the seven [University] colleges [â€¦]. â€˜Yung Kalayaan means the freedom of education that we are attaining right now,â€ the student-leader said.

The University President Rev. Fr. Marcelo V. Manimtim, CM reminded the students that they have a family in Adamson. 

â€œAng bawat isang estudyante ay dapat makaramdam na siya ay nabibilang sa isang maliit na pamilya. [â€¦] Kung mayroon kayong pangangailangan, sana makalapit kayo sa mga [â€¦] Kuya at Ate [â€¦], professors, [â€¦] offices who pledged that they will try to serve you,â€ he expressed.

Furthermore, a Pharmacy freshie shared her Tatak experience under the opposing weather. 

â€œFeel ko po magkakasakit po ako, pero [â€¦] masaya po na na-experience ko â€˜yung event na â€˜to na may sunshine at may ulan. So, very memorable po,â€ she stated.

Similarly, a freshman Political Science student emphasized that their group â€œoverwhelminglyâ€ felt the Vincentian spirit, especially after receiving their handprint marks. 

Meanwhile, a Psychology fresher highlighted his own interpretation of the ceremony.  

â€œâ€™Yung Tatak is pagtutulungan ng mga Adamsonian. Kasi â€˜di ba kapag Klasmeyt ka, iisa tayo at magtutulungan tayo, walang maiiwan,â€ he described.

The freshmen and transferees first assembled at different points around the University, then marched towards the SV Grounds to receive their blue marks. 

Since its last in 2020, Tatak Adamson 2023: Kakulayaan is a student welcoming event by AUSG, which also featured home-grown talents in a concert.
